1. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with the problem of sampling from the uniform distribution on the set of Eulerian orientations of subgraphs of the triangular lattice, which is a problem in discrete mathematics. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the mixing time of a Markov chain on the Eulerian orientations of a planar graph, which is a problem related to algorithms and data structures. 
3. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with the problem of sampling from the uniform distribution on the set of Eulerian orientations of subgraphs of the triangular lattice, which is a problem related to computational geometry. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper shows that the problem of counting Eulerian orientations remains #P-complete when restricted to planar graphs, which is a problem related to computational complexity. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper discusses the conductance of the Markov chain on the Eulerian orientations of a planar graph, which is a problem related to game theory.
